// Market Research Survey
// Comprehensive market research with dynamic branching based on product usage

> start "Welcome to Our Market Research Survey" "Thank you for taking the time to share your thoughts with us. Your feedback helps us improve our products and services." -> age-group

? age-group Ch* "What is your age group?" [18-24, 25-34, 35-44, 45-54, 55+] -> product-usage

? product-usage Ch* "Do you use our product?" [regularly:"Yes regularly", occasionally:"Yes occasionally", aware:"No but aware", never:"Never heard of it"] -> satisfaction ?in [regularly, occasionally]
  -> why-not-tried ?= aware
  -> product-explanation ?= never

// Branch 1: Active users (regularly or occasionally)
? satisfaction Rt* "How satisfied are you with our product?" "Please rate your overall satisfaction" {min:1, max:5} -> features-used

? features-used Mc "Which features do you use?" "Select all that apply" [analytics:"Analytics Dashboard", reports:"Custom Reports", integrations:"Third-party Integrations", automation:"Workflow Automation", collaboration:"Team Collaboration", mobile:"Mobile App"] -> price-importance

// Branch 2: Aware but haven't tried
? why-not-tried Ch* "Why haven't you tried our product?" [price:"Price", features:"Features", competition:"Competition", other:"Other"] -> price-importance

// Branch 3: Never heard of it
! product-explanation "About Our Product" "Our product is a comprehensive business intelligence platform that helps companies make data-driven decisions. It offers analytics, reporting, automation, and collaboration features designed to streamline your workflow and improve productivity." -> interested-trying

? interested-trying Ch* "Are you interested in trying our product?" [yes:"Yes", no:"No"] -> price-importance

// Common questions (all paths merge here)
? price-importance Sl* "How important is price when choosing a solution like ours?" "Move the slider from 0 (not important) to 100 (very important)" {min:0, max:100, step:1, showValue:true} -> feedback

? feedback Tx "Do you have any additional feedback or suggestions?" "Your insights are valuable to us" {placeholder:"Share your thoughts here..."} -> end

< end "Thank You!" "We appreciate your time and feedback. Your responses will help us improve our products and services."
